properties.name: Embarcadero Speedway
properties.description: Posted by PaloaltohistoryAs the connection road between the 101 and El Camino Real, Embarcadero Road has become a kind of psychological extension of the Bayshore Freeway. But for the residents who have the 110 odd driveways along the road, it is a constant battle to keep drivers aware that it is a residential street. Over the years in an attempt to slow down those who consistently treat Embarcadero like a freeway, the city has erected a dizzying array of "slow down" signs, flashing signs that tell you your speed and endless reminders that the road has a 25 mph limit. Police can now use radar on parts of Embarcadero, but before 2001 is was prohibited by state law. The 25 mph speed limit and 38 mph average speed would have designated it as a "speed trap" according to state law. When police asked that the speed limit be raised to 35 so they could get out the speed guns, residents were solidly opposed. Similar debates took place over the speed limits on Alma, Middlefield and Arastradero. Over the years, the city has come up with all sorts of ideas to slow drivers down other than tickets. At one point, the council seriously studied cutting the road to one lane in each direction and placing roundabouts down its length (the .5 million pricetag slowed that plan down). Median strips and bike lanes have also been called for repeatedly. But still, the road remains the same---a small morality test for drivers each day who must ignore a barriage of slow down reminders as they speed their way to and fro the 101.

properties.description: Posted by ParkerburnmillVancouver will be the capitol of Cascadia. sorry G... John McLoughin "The Father of Oregon" - Van-cruiser. 3-6-0 nucka Oregon Trail has two endings. If you go over the land route you end in Oregon City if you shoot the cascades you end in Fort Vancouver. Both endings have the same pic of Mt. Hood! Vancouver Wa. would have to be the capitol of Cascadia for many different reasons. a) we would have to establish a new graffic standard in architecture. We require vast open spaces that are accessable to the populace. This new spectacle should have some sort of historic barometer to bolster the foundation of the Cascadian icon. Vancouver is by no doubt the center of metropolitan growth from Yeurba Buena (San Fransisco/Oakland) to Vancouver Island. b) We have to acknowledge the power of the Columbia. It is the source of our economic fortitude. Deep ports, Hydroelectricity and nature conservation would all be priority issues and should be give the respect that only Vancouver is able to exemplify. c)Vancouver is a symbolic military post. Marshall and Roosevelt drafted the Pacific Theatre of Operations from Vancouver. Some argue that the Army AirForce was sharpened as a tactical weapon at Peirson Airport. When the Russians came west on the first transpolar flight they landed in Vancouver. The Kaiser Liberty ships were built on this side of the river. d) even the beer industry was started by the Nor\'Westers and Hudson\'s Bay employees (Vancouver) e) We got the Ross Complex and the rest of the BPA infrastructure. Trojan is in Oregon. The capitol is not as interesting as taking all the fissionable and radioactive material in the region and loading it onto freight trains. Drive it up past the continental divide and unhook the box cars. They moved the reactor but the spent fuel rods are on your side of the River. Cascadia would portion resources for the construction of monoliths and architectural nuevo. Avante garde physical environments and organic preservation that is considerably more harmonious than the current thread of thought. Ban GMO\'s, redesign hydroelectric harvesting, upgrade and prolong the life span of infrastructure, build a high speed train from Alaska to San Fransisco, erect skyscrapers that lay down into draw bridges, suspend domes over neighborhoods. Sponsor safe, efficient and profitable space tourism. Build swimming pools with four story water slides in everyones backyard.
